          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Create and configure a filter that produces an image processing effect,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "like adding a drop shadow or a blur effect, by calling one of the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "factory methods defined by the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Filter",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " structure. Call the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/GraphicsContext/addFilter(_:options:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method to add the filter to a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/GraphicsContext",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". The filter only affects content that you draw",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "into the context after adding the filter.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
